non_residential_details.development_type: Change of Use with Extension(s) over 999sqm

description: The retention and alteration of Wallis House in association with the re-instatement of employment use (Class B1), the creation of a gallery (Class D1) the provision of a health club (Class D2) and the introduction of residential use (Class C3) of the building. The retention, alteration and extension of International House and its use as a restaurant (Class A3) and incubator business units (Class B1). The demolition of all other buildings on the site and redevelopment for mixed employment (Class A1, A2, A3, A4, B1 and C1), community (Class D1 and D2) and private and affordable residential (Class C3-dwellinghouses) use, together with associated public and private open space & 690 car parking and landscaping.
